title: What is the Free Trade Area of the Asia-Pacific?
description:
APEC member economies account for 40 percent of the world's population and generate 53 percent of the global economic output. Two years ago, APEC members agreed to take steps towards regional integration with a Free Trade Area of the Asia-Pacific (FTAAP). Check the video to find out more about FTAAP.
